# Cursor Rules for sfparty

## CRITICAL: Test File Execution Rules

### test/lib/file/fileIO.test.ts - NEVER RUN WITHOUT TIMEOUT

**ABSOLUTE RULE**: The test file `test/lib/file/fileIO.test.ts` MUST NEVER be run in isolation without a timeout command.

**Why**: This test file hangs indefinitely when run in isolation due to test framework mock setup quirks. It works correctly when run as part of the full test suite (`bun run test:coverage`).

**Required Command Format**:
```bash
timeout 10 bun test test/lib/file/fileIO.test.ts [other args]
```

**NEVER DO THIS**:
- ❌ `bun test test/lib/file/fileIO.test.ts`
- ❌ `bun test test/lib/file/fileIO.test.ts -t "test name"`
- ❌ Any command that runs this file without `timeout`

**ALWAYS DO THIS**:
- ✅ `timeout 10 bun test test/lib/file/fileIO.test.ts`
- ✅ `bun run test:coverage` (runs all tests, works fine)
- ✅ `bun test` (runs all tests, works fine)

**If you need to test changes to fileIO.test.ts**:
1. Make your changes
2. Run the FULL test suite: `bun run test:coverage`
3. If that passes, your changes are good
4. DO NOT run the file in isolation

**This rule is PERMANENT and MUST be followed. Violating this rule causes the test to hang indefinitely.**

